_Original author: jakob.malm (December 06, 2011 10:23:24)_

Is it possible to write null-terminated, fixed-length strings in a compound data structure? The following datatype is what I'm aiming for:

DATATYPE  H5T_COMPOUND {
   H5T_STRING {
      STRSIZE 64;
      STRPAD H5T_STR_NULLTERM;
      CSET H5T_CSET_ASCII;
      CTYPE H5T_C_S1;
   } &quot;id&quot;;
   H5T_STRING {
      STRSIZE 64;
      STRPAD H5T_STR_NULLTERM;
      CSET H5T_CSET_ASCII;
      CTYPE H5T_C_S1;
   } &quot;name&quot;;
...
}

The following gives me null-padded, fixed-length strings:

&gt;&gt;&gt; dt = np.dtype([('id', '|S64'), ('name', '|S64')]) # I also have other types, floats, ints, in the real compound
&gt;&gt;&gt; a = np.array(('sswe', 'Southern Sweden'), dtype=dt)
&gt;&gt;&gt; f.create_dataset('region', data=dt)

h5dump:
HDF5 &quot;tmp.h5&quot; {
GROUP &quot;/&quot; {
   DATASET &quot;region&quot; {
      DATATYPE  H5T_COMPOUND {
         H5T_STRING {
            STRSIZE 64;
            STRPAD H5T_STR_NULLPAD;
            CSET H5T_CSET_ASCII;
            CTYPE H5T_C_S1;
         } &quot;id&quot;;
         H5T_STRING {
            STRSIZE 64;
            STRPAD H5T_STR_NULLPAD;
            CSET H5T_CSET_ASCII;
            CTYPE H5T_C_S1;
         } &quot;name&quot;;
      }
      DATASPACE  SCALAR
      DATA {
      (0): {
            &quot;sswe\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000&quot;,
            &quot;Southern Sweden\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000\000&quot;
         }
      }
   }
}
}

The following gives me null-terminated, variable-length strings:

&gt;&gt;&gt; vstr = h5py.special_datatype(vlen=str)
&gt;&gt;&gt; dt = np.dtype([('id', vstr), ('name', vstr)])
&gt;&gt;&gt; a = np.array(('sswe', 'Southern Sweden'), dtype=dt)
&gt;&gt;&gt; f.create_dataset('region', data=a)

h5dump:
HDF5 &quot;tmp.h5&quot; {
GROUP &quot;/&quot; {
   DATASET &quot;region&quot; {
      DATATYPE  H5T_COMPOUND {
         H5T_STRING {
            STRSIZE H5T_VARIABLE;
            STRPAD H5T_STR_NULLTERM;
            CSET H5T_CSET_ASCII;
            CTYPE H5T_C_S1;
         } &quot;id&quot;;
         H5T_STRING {
            STRSIZE H5T_VARIABLE;
            STRPAD H5T_STR_NULLTERM;
            CSET H5T_CSET_ASCII;
            CTYPE H5T_C_S1;
         } &quot;name&quot;;
      }
      DATASPACE  SCALAR
      DATA {
      (0): {
            &quot;sswe&quot;,
            &quot;Southern Sweden&quot;
         }
      }
   }
}
}

RHEL 6
Python 2.6
h5py 1.4.0-beta2 (easy_install'ed, numpy 1.5.1)
HDF5 1.8.5

